                                                                              org.apache.commons.math3.geometry.euclidean.threed.Vector3D goalPosition,

        Dijkstra's algorithm [1]. [1] E. W. Dijkstra. (1959). "A note on two problems in connexion with graphs". Numer. Math. 1, 1 (December 1959), 269-271. doi:10.1007/BF01386390.
        Specified by:
        findPath in class AbstractPathFinder
        Parameters:
        startPosition - the Cartesian coordinates of the starting node.
        goalPosition - the Cartesian coordinates of the destination node.
        timeout - the amount of time at most a pathfinder can attempt to find a path.
        Returns:
        if a path is found returns, an array of Vector3D coordinates of the points to go from an start to an target position. Otherwise returns NULL.
